hannel and pattern subscriptions and records the writer. The resubscription process successfully invokes `toArray` with `Array.newInstance` for both SUBSCRIBE and PSUBSCRIBE. \\\\n\\\\nNote that I didn't run any tests as per instructions. Also, there's something to consider: if `connection.close()` throws an error, then `writer.shutdownClientResources()` won't execute. I wonder if a robust nested try might help, but maybe it's not necessary.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Ensuring resource shutdown**\\\\n\\\\nI'm checking the code for proper shutdown procedures, and it looks like using `finally { shutdown }` is a great way to ensure that resources are cleaned up. I'm also considering the `InterruptedException` to handle any interruptions that might occur during the shutdown process effectively. This addition makes me feel better since it ensures that resources will still shut down even if something unexpectedly throws an exception. It's all about reliability!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_Fm5MilnHSsiZUEhpePPVnPF6|fc_0377e634e9976fa40169f9eabd638c819fa3f44dcbc99f67a4\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/io.lettuce/lettuce-core/6.2.6.RELEASE/src/test/java/io_lettuce/lettuce_core/StatefulRedisPubSubConnectionImplTest.java\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"        } finally {\\n            if (connection != null) {\\n                connection.close();\\n            }\\n            writer.shutdownClientResources();\\n        }\\n\", \"newText\": \"        } finally {\\n            try {\\n                if (connection != null) {\\n                    connection.close();\\n                }\\n            } finally {\\n                writer.shutdownClientResources();\\n            }\\n        }\\n\"}]}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 702, \"output\": 696, \"cacheRead\": 45568, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 46966, \"cost\": {